   <text>
      <body>
         <opener><dateline><date when="1921-03-02">March 2, 1921.</date></dateline>
            <salute>Dear <persName key="hilda_doolittle">Hilda</persName>:</salute></opener>
         <p>This is just a little line to send you the royalties cheque which I forgot to send from
            <placeName key="newHaven">New Haven</placeName>, as I promised. It is not, as you see, very grand. The amount is as follows:</lb>
            By sales</lb>
            27 <title key="some_imagist_poets">Imagist Poets</title>, 1915 .67 1/2 $18.22</lb>
            23 “ “ 1916 .67 1/2 15.52</lb>
            22 “ “ 1917 .67 1/2 14.85</lb>
            48.59</lb>
            one sixth of $48.59 is <measure type="currency" num="$8.09">$8.09</measure></p>
         <p>I hope you got over safely. I will not write any more now as I am trying to get things
            off and return to <placeName key="nyc">New York</placeName> to-morrow. How I wish you were to be there. We did enjoy
            seeing each other, didn’t we?</p>
         <p>Give lots of love to <persName key="winifred_bryher">Winifred</persName>, and tell me how things stand from your own point of
            view.</p>
         <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>

         <p>Enclosure.</p>

      </body>
